00:06:45.690 --> 00:06:49.620
as as soon as you get on to the editing part
of the

00:06:49.620 --> 00:06:58.840
post, what happens really and how, what are
the challenges that I faced.

00:06:58.840 --> 00:07:04.480
So, so how to work with Gutenberg using a
screen reader. We will be walking through

00:07:04.480 --> 00:07:09.920
a demo and the usability challenges and and
then the some of the accessibility challenges

00:07:09.920 --> 00:07:16.340
that I have seen in Gutenberg.

00:07:16.340 --> 00:07:23.020
So what is Gutenberg? So Gutenberg is the
introduced in WordPress 5.0. It is a rich

00:07:23.020 --> 00:07:30.979
uh editor and in my perspective, what I have
seen is that you basically being used to create

00:07:30.979 --> 00:07:36.160
a rich content. When I say rich content, it's
not just headings, lists, paragraphs, great

00:07:36.160 --> 00:07:43.360
design also. The topography, all the layouts
and and it has evolved. Like it came into

00:07:43.360 --> 00:07:49.970
existence in WordPress 5.0 and right now the
version WordPress 5.5 is running, and the

00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:58.040
core uh Gutenberg plugin gets updated every
two, once in two weeks. And with every major

00:07:58.040 --> 00:08:02.440
update the core is merged into WordPress core.

00:08:02.440 --> 00:08:11.759
So what I have seen is there's a collection
of blogs, when initially the collection of,

00:08:11.759 --> 00:08:17.580
when everyone started talking about Gutenberg
and the saying, it's a block based design.

00:08:17.580 --> 00:08:22.830
As a person with disability I did not understand
what is a block. So I, I when I was reading

00:08:22.830 --> 00:08:30.389
articles on other blogs and websites they
said heading block, paragraph block or you

00:08:30.389 --> 00:08:35.430
know all the list block. I did not understand
what is a block.

00:08:35.430 --> 00:08:39.990
Theoretically it was very difficult to understand
what was a block.

00:08:39.990 --> 00:08:46.830
Then when I started working with Gutenberg,
then I got a clear picture that every section

00:08:46.830 --> 00:08:55.690
of the content area is designated a block,
is called a block. Like you you create a heading,

00:08:55.690 --> 00:09:04.290
it is a block on its own. It, you have a paragraph,
it's a block on its own. And Gutenberg gives

00:09:04.290 --> 00:09:10.320
a lot of control over the content and the
layout of these blocks.

00:09:10.320 --> 00:09:21.779
So you can customize all the font size, colour
uh and styling of all the fonts and all. So

00:09:21.779 --> 00:09:27.120
these are some of the options that I have
seen and uh from the technical standpoint

00:09:27.120 --> 00:09:32.839
like for a person with visual disability,
it was not very useful for me to go and edit,

00:09:32.839 --> 00:09:38.040
because I'm not sure what exactly, what the
color is going to be on the front end. And

00:09:38.040 --> 00:09:52.650
also I normally generally use the basic themes
settings that are there.

00:09:52.650 --> 00:09:57.390
So we all know that the Gutenberg accessibility
story, it's merged with 5.0.

00:09:57.390 --> 00:10:07.200
There was a lot of push back from the accessibility
community and a lot of accessibility professionals

00:10:07.200 --> 00:10:12.870
and the wider community itself said that it
should not be merged with 5.0, because it's

00:10:12.870 --> 00:10:17.130
not mature.
And what, there were a lot of articles on

00:10:17.130 --> 00:10:22.440
the web where it was told that it was written,

00:10:22.440 --> 00:10:30.180
like the design aspect, like accessibility
is not considered from the start. But what

00:10:30.180 --> 00:10:38.709
I see is for, with a two week, every two weeks
development cycle and being pushed every two

00:10:38.709 --> 00:10:44.330
weeks, it's very difficult to keep up with
both accessibility design, development, and

00:10:44.330 --> 00:10:49.300
fixes of accessibility bugs and all that.
So there were a lot of challenges because

00:10:49.300 --> 00:10:56.670
there were a lot of moving parts, but uh after
two years,

00:10:56.670 --> 00:11:03.650
after two years and what happened in 2019
is a WP Campus called for an independent audit

00:11:03.650 --> 00:11:09.440
by an agency, and the agency provided it results
and we had like close to 300 accessibility

00:11:09.440 --> 00:11:18.140
bugs that were found, that that were found
on the Gutenberg. And the Gutenberg was audited,

00:11:18.140 --> 00:11:26.820
not on the plug-in, but was in the core that
was merged with WordPress. So what did the

00:11:26.820 --> 00:11:32.000
WP Campus audit show? It showed like considerable
amount of accessibility bugs.

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:38.020
There were more than 300 accessibility bugs.
Like couple of more of these bugs were related

00:11:38.020 --> 00:11:45.400
to authoring tool where you upload a video
and there were no there is no way to provide

00:11:45.400 --> 00:11:46.400
caption.

00:11:46.400 --> 00:11:53.690
So some of these are authoring tool challenges
and some of them are pure accessibility bugs.

00:11:53.690 --> 00:12:01.950
And after the WP Campus audit there are a
lot of bug fixes on the way and the accessibility

00:12:01.950 --> 00:12:06.800
team started, the development team started
fixing a lot of these accessibility bugs.

00:12:06.800 --> 00:12:13.740
And we have seen, I've personally seen some
of these accessibility fix being uh, in place,

00:12:13.740 --> 00:12:20.589
during the subsequent Gutenberg plugin releases
and in the core merge also.

00:12:20.589 --> 00:12:26.570
And if you go to GitHub, I, I provided the
link here. There are a couple of significant

00:12:26.570 --> 00:12:34.360
more accessibility bugs still that are open.
And some of these bugs are, you know, like

00:12:34.360 --> 00:12:41.540
pure technical related maybe as a person with
disability you might not be uh finding it

00:12:41.540 --> 00:12:46.790
very difficult to navigate, but they are technically
an accessibility bug, that's why they are

00:12:46.790 --> 00:12:52.019
called upon.

00:12:52.019 --> 00:12:57.800
So what, how Gutenberg is uh,

00:12:57.800 --> 00:13:03.600
very difficult, like, as I said in the previously,
it's very difficult for screen reader users.

00:13:03.600 --> 00:13:10.240
So what I did is as a person with visual disability,
I work with a lot of other people with disability

00:13:10.240 --> 00:13:15.899
uh in the local community, so me and couple
of uh my friends who are all screen reader

00:13:15.899 --> 00:13:22.690
users and some of these people are accessibility
specialists, so what what I did, I gave them

00:13:22.690 --> 00:13:30.959
the Guten, I installed the Gutenberg plug-in
and we, I I studied them how they're going

00:13:30.959 --> 00:13:33.830
to use.
And some of the power screen reader users

00:13:33.830 --> 00:13:36.910
found it very difficult. They they did not
understand,

00:13:36.910 --> 00:13:42.360
but like, the there are a lot of elements
like, as soon as you open the post screen

00:13:42.360 --> 00:13:43.399
add new post screen,

00:13:43.399 --> 00:13:49.050
there are lot of elements and you click on
add block and your focus moves to a search

00:13:49.050 --> 00:13:55.010
field.
So there they are like caught off guard completely.

00:13:55.010 --> 00:13:59.270
So we are going to discuss some of these during
the demo. Like I'll be running a demo of how

00:13:59.270 --> 00:14:06.160
I use Gutenberg and how you know,
it is very different from our Classic Editor.

00:14:06.160 --> 00:14:10.649
What happens in our Classic Editor is like
you have the title screen and there you have

00:14:10.649 --> 00:14:14.630
the content area where you type in the content.

00:14:14.630 --> 00:14:21.110
Or generally what happens is as a person with
disability, we generally use uh Microsoft

00:14:21.110 --> 00:14:28.070
Word and we type in our content and then we
put it in the Classic Editor and we use screen

00:14:28.070 --> 00:14:34.880
uh shortcut keys in the Classic Editor to
give a heading paragraph and block code and

00:14:34.880 --> 00:14:43.950
other markup to these, to the content that
we created. So it was pretty easy for us and

00:14:43.950 --> 00:14:46.370
some of them you know said

00:14:46.370 --> 00:14:55.640
that, we know HTML, so what they do is they
use the Classic Editor text, text mode instead

00:14:55.640 --> 00:15:01.020
of visual editor and they mark up the content
directly in Microsoft Word and they just put

00:15:01.020 --> 00:15:08.680
it in the editor and just publish the content.
And that's where you know as a screen reader

00:15:08.680 --> 00:15:16.790
user it needs a lot of learning curve here.
And it, it's a lot of visual aspect Gutenberg,

00:15:16.790 --> 00:15:24.029
as I said, earlier uh. It's,
it's there to create great visual design,

00:15:24.029 --> 00:15:30.200
but as a person with disability and who has
been writing content for more than 12,12 to

00:15:30.200 --> 00:15:36.899
14 years uh, I did not find it, like for me
it's just headings, paragraph, it's more of

00:15:36.899 --> 00:15:43.180
content than visual aspect of the [unintelligible].

00:15:43.180 --> 00:15:48.660
So one, one of the challenges that we also
faced is with regard to the block definitions.

00:15:48.660 --> 00:15:55.290
So some of the blocks, like if you go out
onto the Gutenberg search area and go category

00:15:55.290 --> 00:16:00.730
by category, there are some of these blocks
like markdown block or uh some of the code

00:16:00.730 --> 00:16:07.660
or you know it's a separator or so there are
some of these blocks that we we did not understand,

00:16:07.660 --> 00:16:14.550
what it, what exactly that block does. Okay
so some of these blocks for which we tried

00:16:14.550 --> 00:16:19.519
to find definition and we were not able to
find. So we felt that you know, if there is

00:16:19.519 --> 00:16:24.310
a help what exactly this block does? Like
how it is going to show up in the front end?

00:16:24.310 --> 00:16:30.760
It would have been very helpful for us to
use some of these blocks.

